props.text: WHAAAT?! I can rent a car for this price! Taxi drivers like to cheat...
It’s quite expensive but I can afford it
I'll hardly find a better price... I guess... but...

That's a very good price! Let's go!
(^_^)
The carousel is free to enter, Foxy!
Jump to the carousel, young lady!
I just want to talk, little fox. Just for a couple of minutes.  Then I’ll stop the wheel and let you go...
...I’m an old man now, nobody wants to speak with me and sometimes I feel lonely. All my friends passed away… I miss the good old days…

I remember all women I met, I love all of them but now I’ve got only a crazy old wife and she’s not as good as she once was.
You understand me, eh?

I used to be a captain. It wasn’t as fun as it’s written in the books but still fun. Sometimes I still hear the sea in my dreams… Well, enough of you, foxy? You can go now but exit isn’t free. You must pay 10 coins.
Life is like a carousel; it goes up and down, round and round, then it can suddenly stop and you are flung from it.
Watch out! All drivers are barmy nowadays. Nobody follows the rules.
No no... "Barmy" is "mad, crazy"! People always complain about mad drivers.
Excuse me. How can I get to Trafalgar  Square?
Dunno. But you can buy a balloon  for 5 coins. It can be useful...
Not right. Dunno is short for Don't Know.
You can buy a balloon from the balloon seller for 5 coins to use it later.
Good day, sir. How can I get to Trafalgar Square?
No... "The gen" means "to request some information".
Nothing here… Except an old rusty hammer. I’ll take it. It might be useful in some way.
Fresh kebab! Made from the best lamb meat!
Mommy told me you make it from cats sometimes.
Not right... "Put a sock in it" means a request to be quiet.
Сheck the meat? Buy kebab for 10 coins?
Give the balloon to the boy?
You're so kind. Here is a free kebab for you, young lady.
